Name: chorioamnionitis
Definition: A placenta disease that is an inflammation of the fetal membranes (amnion and chorion) due to a bacterial infection.

Name: placenta praevia
Definition: A placenta disease that is characterized by placenta attachment to the uterine wall close to or covering the cervix.

Name: oligohydramnios
Definition: A placenta disease that is characterized by a deficiency of amniotic fluid sometimes resulting in an embryonic defect through adherence between embryo and amnion.

Name: placenta cancer
Definition: A female reproductive organ cancer that is located_in the placenta.

Name: obsolete metastatic neoplasm to the placenta
Definition: A female reproductive organ cancer that is located_in the placenta.

Name: chorioangioma
Definition: A specific developmental disorder that is characterized by the persistent presence of involuntary brief movements or sounds occuring intermittently and unpredictably out of a background of normal motor activity.

Name: obsolete diaper rash
Definition: A specific developmental disorder that is characterized by the persistent presence of involuntary brief movements or sounds occuring intermittently and unpredictably out of a background of normal motor activity.

Name: obsolete atopic dermatitis and related conditions
Definition: A specific developmental disorder that is characterized by the persistent presence of involuntary brief movements or sounds occuring intermittently and unpredictably out of a background of normal motor activity.

Name: placental insufficiency
Definition: A placenta disease that is characterized by insufficient blood flow to the placenta during pregnancy.

Name: placenta accreta
Definition: A placenta disease that is characterized by an abnormally deep attachment of the placenta
Synonym: mixed germ cell tumor of testis

Name: obsolete olfaction disorder
Definition: A placenta disease that is characterized by an abnormally deep attachment of the placenta

Name: obsolete childhood supratentorial neoplasm
Definition: A placenta disease that is characterized by an abnormally deep attachment of the placenta

Name: polyhydramnios
Definition: A placenta disease that is characterized by an excess of amniotic fluid in the amniotic sac.

Name: obsolete disorder of amniotic fluid and membranes
Definition: A placenta disease that is characterized by an excess of amniotic fluid in the amniotic sac.

Name: placental abruption
Definition: A placenta disease that is characterized by separation of the placental lining from the uterus of the mother.
